              "id": "QUE62770",
              "question": "An elementary school teacher told her class that children with brown eyes are smarter and work harder than children with blue eyes. To impress upon the students the difference between them, the teacher pinned a piece of brown or blue cloth on each child according to his or her eye color. In short order, the brown-eyed children acted superior to the blue-eyed children, performing better in class and treating the blue-eyed children as inferior. In addition, the blue-eyed children began to act inferior and underperformed in class. In sociological terms, this experiment best demonstrates __________.\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
